has his paw prints all over it.

137
00:07:23,176 --> 00:07:24,974
There's no bad blood.

138
00:07:28,415 --> 00:07:31,783
CHAPMAN: You attacked him at the
Goodhew Awards a couple of months ago.

139
00:07:31,851 --> 00:07:33,046
He attacked me.

140
00:07:33,119 --> 00:07:34,348
That's not what I heard.

141
00:07:34,421 --> 00:07:36,913
Well, you heard it wrong,
Chapman. You always do.

142
00:07:36,990 --> 00:07:40,187
I would say it's your big failing,
but you have so many.

143
00:07:40,260 --> 00:07:43,491
What about the altercation
that took place last Thursday?

144
00:07:43,563 --> 00:07:45,258
That Monckton's fault, too?

145
00:07:45,332 --> 00:07:48,700
Yes. Every time I run into the guy,
he's all over me.

146
00:07:48,768 --> 00:07:51,396
He keeps accusing me
of trying to steal his clients.

147
00:07:51,471 --> 00:07:53,030
