Before, he couldn't
take his hands off me.

237
00:11:47,674 --> 00:11:51,372
I even know who it is.
All I need is proof.

238
00:11:51,444 --> 00:11:53,242
Mrs. Gustavo...

239
00:11:53,313 --> 00:11:54,337
(SIGHS)

240
00:11:54,414 --> 00:11:57,816
...you don't know how
difficult this is for me, but,

241
00:11:57,884 --> 00:12:01,445
much as I'd like to help you,
I don't handle domestic cases.

242
00:12:04,624 --> 00:12:06,422
It isn't a question of money.

243
00:12:06,492 --> 00:12:11,293
I know. You think if you give me proof,
I'm gonna go crazy,

244
00:12:11,364 --> 00:12:13,332
and I'm gonna kill my
husband. I 'am not...

245
00:12:13,399 --> 00:12:15,993
Well, no, I... ...going to kill my husband,
Mr. Rockford.

246
00:12:16,102 --> 00:12:19,367
I am not even going to kill
that tramp from the office.

247
00:12:19,439 --> 00:12:22,465
He's going to fire her
and never see her again.

248
00:12:23,743 --> 00:12:27,077
I have been married
for 12 years.

249
00:12:27,146 --> 00:12:32,209
Do you think I am going to let Eleanor
Hooperman just walk off with Hector?

250
00:12:32,285 --> 00:12:36,153
Mrs. Gustavo,
when I went into this business years ago,

251
00:12:36,222 --> 00:12:38,054
I made just one promise
to myself.

252
00:12:38,124 --> 00:12:40,058
No domestic cases.

253
00:12:40,126 --> 00:12:42,993
Now, I've never broken that promise,
and I don't intend to now.

254
00:12:43,062 --> 00:12:44,962
No matter how much
I'd like to help you...

255
00:12:45,031 --> 00:12:47,523
No, no. Don't do that.
Now, don't do that.

256
00:12:47,600 --> 00:12:52,834
That's way too much. There are
some very good people out there.

257
00:12:52,905 --> 00:12:55,237
They're easy to
talk to, discreet.

258
00:12:55,308 --> 00:12:56,833
I'd be happy to refer someone.

259
00:12:56,909 --> 00:12:58,775
Why don't I
just kill myself?

260
00:12:58,845 --> 00:13:01,712
I'd rather be dead
than run all over town,

261
00:13:01,781 --> 00:13:04,375
telling total strangers
about my sex life.

262
00:13:04,450 --> 00:13:05,713
I'm a total stranger.

263
00:13:05,785 --> 00:13:08,584
No, you're not.
You know Randy.

264
00:13:08,655 --> 00:13:10,145
Now, you said
you weren't going to cry.

265
00:13:10,223 --> 00:13:11,850
(CRYING) I can't help it.

266
00:13:13,026 --> 00:13:15,085
You took Randy's money.

267
00:13:16,029 --> 00:13:17,895
Why won't you take mine?

268
00:13:19,232 --> 00:13:22,463
You don't know how difficult
you're making this for me.

269
00:13:22,535 --> 00:13:24,867
(STUTTERING) I mean,
as much as I'd like to help you,

270
00:13:24,937 --> 00:13:28,339
this just isn't my kind
of case. Not at all.

271
00:13:28,408 --> 00:13:29,432
(PHONE RINGING)

272
00:13:29,509 --> 00:13:31,807
That's not your
kind of case?

273
00:13:32,512 --> 00:13:34,310
Sure, it is.

274
00:13:34,380 --> 00:13:36,041
What'd you do for
the lady, Rockford?

275
00:13:36,115 --> 00:13:37,981
Break into some
cheesy hotel room

276
00:13:38,051 --> 00:13:42,750
with a photographer,
catching Gustavo in flagrante delicto?

277
00:13:42,855 --> 00:13:45,984
Yeah, me and Lyle Talbot,
we work as a team.

278
00:13:46,059 --> 00:13:47,652
Does he have to be here?

279
00:13:47,727 --> 00:13:49,126
Yes.

280
00:13:50,196 --> 00:13:53,496
Can we get some
decent coffee in here?

281
00:13:55,068 --> 00:13:56,433
Good idea.

282
00:13:56,502 --> 00:13:59,665
So, you got hired
by Linda Gustavo

283
00:13:59,739 --> 00:14:01,400
to get the goods
on her old man.

284
00:14:01,474 --> 00:14:03,408
And you did this
by following him?

285
00:14:03,476 --> 00:14:04,910
Well, I followed him, yeah.

286
00:14:04,977 --> 00:14:08,003
I also got a job at his record company,
Felicidad Records.

287
00:14:08,081 --> 00:14:11,016
Which is where you had the
confrontation with Bud Monckton.

288
00:14:11,084 --> 00:14:13,553
No, which is where he had
his confrontation with me.

289
00:14:13,619 --> 00:14:17,886
The guy's paranoid. I...
He runs security for them.

290
00:14:17,957 --> 00:14:19,755
He thought I was trying
to steal the account.

291
00:14:19,826 --> 00:14:24,161
I was just trying to check up
on Gustavo from the inside.

292
00:14:24,230 --> 00:14:28,030
So, I wrote a few glossy
letters of recommendation.

293
00:14:28,101 --> 00:14:30,263
I got exactly the job
I was shooting for.

294
00:14:30,336 --> 00:14:33,829
It gave me unquestioned access
to the whole complex,

295
00:14:33,906 --> 00:14:37,069
and at the same time
it rendered me invisible.

296
00:14:38,544 --> 00:14:42,003
RECEPTIONIST: Felicidad Records. I'm sorry,
she's not in...

297
00:14:42,081 --> 00:14:45,574
So, did you finish the copy? He's
going to be asking for it, you know.

298
00:14:45,651 --> 00:14:46,743
It's on his desk.

299
00:14:46,819 --> 00:14:49,789
He'll probably want me to
rewrite it before lunch. Again.

300
00:14:49,856 --> 00:14:50,846
ELEANOR:
He's a perfectionist.

301
00:14:50,923 --> 00:14:52,186
STRINGER:
He's a control freak.

302
00:14:52,258 --> 00:14:53,748
Yeah. That, too.

303
00:14:53,826 --> 00:14:55,624
I'm going to say no.

304
00:14:57,430 --> 00:15:01,162
Hey, I'm the writer. I'm not
going to let him ruin my work.

305
00:15:01,834 --> 00:15:03,461
(UPBEAT MUSIC PLAYING)

306
00:15:03,536 --> 00:15:05,698
Come in, come in.
Sit down.

307
00:15:13,045 --> 00:15:18,347
I've been going over your copy,
Sam. It's just not there.

308
00:15:18,418 --> 00:15:21,854
You know,
there's no juice in it. No excitement.

309
00:15:21,921 --> 00:15:25,789
What you hear in the music,
that's what I want in the words.

310
00:15:26,926 --> 00:15:30,920
I don't know how you can
listen to this and give me that.

311
00:15:30,997 --> 00:15:33,796
I'll have a rewrite for you
when you get back from lunch.

312
00:15:33,866 --> 00:15:35,425
(LAUGHING)

313
00:15:35,501 --> 00:15:37,629
Did I ask for a rewrite? Hmm?

314
00:15:37,703 --> 00:15:39,034
I think that's your
problem right there.

315
00:15:39,105 --> 00:15:42,666
You rewrote the life
out of it. Put it away.

316
00:15:42,742 --> 00:15:45,609
Go back to it in a couple
of days. See what happens.

317
00:15:45,678 --> 00:15:49,478
Look, I know it seems like I've
been beating up on you a lot lately.

318
00:15:49,549 --> 00:15:51,540
Hell, I've been beating up
on everyone.

319
00:15:51,617 --> 00:15:53,915
It's because we've finally
got a shot with this one.

320
00:15:53,986 --> 00:15:55,681
It's gonna take off,
I know it.

321
00:15:55,755 --> 00:15:57,018
You're that sure?

322
00:15:57,089 --> 00:15:59,751
Have I ever said anything like that before,
in all these years?

323
00:15:59,826 --> 00:16:02,989
I think the whole Latin thing
is going to explode.

324
00:16:03,062 --> 00:16:05,531
Go mainstream,
like it did in the '40s.

325
00:16:05,598 --> 00:16:08,795
Carmen Miranda, a major star.

326
00:16:08,868 --> 00:16:12,270
Cugat, he was making movies,
playing clubs,

327
00:16:12,338 --> 00:16:14,534
selling records,
selling chihuahuas.

328
00:16:14,607 --> 00:16:18,043
In the '40s, if it was Latin,
it was happening.

329
00:16:18,110 --> 00:16:19,805
My God, listen to this.

330
00:16:19,879 --> 00:16:21,506
(VOLUME INCREASES)

331
00:16:21,581 --> 00:16:24,175
You got a bunch of monks
all over the charts!

332
00:16:24,250 --> 00:16:26,412
You think that's not
going to go platinum?

333
00:16:26,486 --> 00:16:27,612
(MUSIC STOPS)

334
00:16:27,687 --> 00:16:29,621
(REMOTE CLATTERS)
Come on, let's eat.

335
00:16:29,689 --> 00:16:31,487
Can we go someplace
besides Rex's?

336
00:16:31,557 --> 00:16:33,685
(LAUGHING) People fight
to get into that place,

337
00:16:33,759 --> 00:16:35,056
and you got a problem with it.

338
00:16:35,127 --> 00:16:37,027
You know, executives
all over the world

339
00:16:37,096 --> 00:16:39,121
take courses on how
to avoid trouble.

340
00:16:39,198 --> 00:16:40,393
They vary their
work schedules,

341
00:16:40,466 --> 00:16:41,661
vary the routes
they travel.

342
00:16:41,734 --> 00:16:42,792
So? I do that.

343
00:16:42,869 --> 00:16:45,361
You also have lunch at the same time,
at the same restaurant,

344
00:16:45,438 --> 00:16:48,271
and at the same table
every single day.

345
00:16:48,341 --> 00:16:50,708
If anyone, anyone,
wanted to get you,

346
00:16:50,776 --> 00:16:52,904
they wouldn't have to set
up some elaborate ambush.

347
00:16:52,979 --> 00:16:54,413
They could just wait
for you at Rex's.

348
00:16:54,480 --> 00:16:55,709
Nobody wants to get me.

349
00:16:55,781 --> 00:16:58,409
Unless it's someone who
bought one of our earlier releases.

350
00:16:58,484 --> 00:17:01,681
(SIGHS) My God,
20 years of nose flutes and clam shells,

351
00:17:01,754 --> 00:17:04,416
and Amazonian
goatherd choirs.

352
00:17:04,490 --> 00:17:06,857
Get the baseboards, okay?
Last guy did a lousy job.

353
00:17:06,926 --> 00:17:09,190
And be out of here
by the time we get back.

354
00:17:11,464 --> 00:17:12,625
(DOOR CLOSING)

355
00:17:30,783 --> 00:17:33,616
Rockford. What the hell
are you doing here?

356
00:17:33,686 --> 00:17:34,881
(EXHALES)

357
00:17:34,954 --> 00:17:38,584
A remedial reading course would
open up whole new worlds for you, Bud.

358
00:17:38,658 --> 00:17:41,218
Oh, sure, you're building
maintenance, right?

359
00:17:41,294 --> 00:17:42,819
What am I, stupid?

360
00:17:42,895 --> 00:17:45,057
I never swing
at the easy ones.

361
00:17:45,131 --> 00:17:48,294
You can tell me,
or you can tell the cops.

362
00:17:48,367 --> 00:17:49,357
I'm gonna call 'em.

363
00:17:49,435 --> 00:17:50,766
Well, good idea.

364
00:17:50,836 --> 00:17:53,362
I'll tell 'em what I'm doing here,
you tell 'em what you're doing.

365
00:17:53,439 --> 00:17:55,464
What I'm doing is security.

366
00:17:55,541 --> 00:17:57,942
Oh, you're going to have a
hard time making that one fly.

367
00:17:58,010 --> 00:18:00,206
Security doesn't hang
bugs on the boss.

368
00:18:00,279 --> 00:18:02,407
Why'd you say that?
Did you find something?

369
00:18:02,481 --> 00:18:05,712
I don't have to find a bug to know
that you've hung 'em all over the place.

370
00:18:05,785 --> 00:18:07,150
It's your M.O., Bud.

371
00:18:07,219 --> 00:18:09,085
Anybody that knows you
knows that.

372
00:18:09,155 --> 00:18:12,125
You know, being stupid and predictable
isn't all it's cracked up to be.

373
00:18:12,191 --> 00:18:14,182
(BOTH GRUNTING)

374
00:18:16,762 --> 00:18:18,230
(ROCKFORD SHOUTING)

375
00:18:29,575 --> 00:18:31,942
How about we go back
to that bad blood

376
00:18:32,011 --> 00:18:33,638
that didn't exist
between the two of you?

377
00:18:33,713 --> 00:18:35,408
You never liked Monckton,
did you, Rockford?

378
00:18:35,481 --> 00:18:37,813
What's to like?
He's a tree with lips.

379
00:18:37,883 --> 00:18:39,476
He's also dead.

380
00:18:44,490 --> 00:18:47,323
You entered his house
at 9:45 p.m.

381
00:18:47,393 --> 00:18:50,419
A disturbance was heard
at 10:30 p.m.

382
00:18:50,496 --> 00:18:53,693
The coroner confirms that
as the probable time of death.

383
00:18:53,766 --> 00:18:57,999
The security camera
never clocked you out.

384
00:18:58,070 --> 00:19:01,404
Look, Monckton called me and
asked me to meet him at his place.

385
00:19:01,474 --> 00:19:02,737
He said he had
some information.

386
00:19:02,808 --> 00:19:04,105
He wanted to make
a deal with me.

387
00:19:04,176 --> 00:19:07,305
When I got there,
the place was empty, so I left.

388
00:19:07,380 --> 00:19:09,075
You expect us to believe that?

389
00:19:09,148 --> 00:19:12,914
Of course not. It's the
truth. I want my attorney.

390
00:19:12,985 --> 00:19:16,512
Sure, fine. Becker can make
the call for you, if you like.

391
00:19:16,589 --> 00:19:17,954
Would you do that, Dennis?

392
00:19:18,057 --> 00:19:20,219
Would you tell her to
get over here, right away?

393
00:19:20,292 --> 00:19:21,760
Who? Kit?

394
00:19:21,827 --> 00:19:24,421
My ex-wife? What the
hell's the matter with you?

395
00:19:24,497 --> 00:19:26,488
Why would I want to
drag her into this?

396
00:19:26,565 --> 00:19:27,999
Beth. Call Beth.

397
00:19:28,067 --> 00:19:29,262
Beth?

398
00:19:29,335 --> 00:19:31,235
Yeah. Call her.

399
00:19:34,440 --> 00:19:36,272
Here, use mine.

400
00:19:36,375 --> 00:19:38,571
You mind telling me
the cause of death?

401
00:19:38,644 --> 00:19:40,669
Like he doesn't know.

402
00:19:40,746 --> 00:19:42,145
He was shot.

403
00:19:42,214 --> 00:19:43,841
BECKER: This is
Lieutenant Becker.

404
00:19:43,916 --> 00:19:49,150
I'd like to have the phone number
for Elizabeth, or Beth Van Sant.

405
00:19:49,221 --> 00:19:51,519
Maiden name, Davenport.

406
00:19:51,590 --> 00:19:53,820
Oh, the listing might be under
her husband's name. Uh...

407
00:19:53,893 --> 00:19:56,225
Roger.
Roger Van Sant.

408
00:19:56,962 --> 00:19:59,522
Yeah, you can try Beverly Hills,
Brent wood, Bel Air,

409
00:19:59,598 --> 00:20:01,430
Holmby...
Pasadena.

410
00:20:01,500 --> 00:20:04,993
Pasadena, even.
Yeah, I'll hold.

411
00:20:05,071 --> 00:20:07,335
What caliber weapon
do you own, Rockford?

412
00:20:12,445 --> 00:20:13,674
.38.

413
00:20:15,981 --> 00:20:18,006
Where is this weapon kept?

414
00:20:19,885 --> 00:20:20,977
(SIGHS)

415
00:20:22,455 --> 00:20:23,718
Lieutenant?

416
00:20:25,024 --> 00:20:26,458
In the cookie jar.

417
00:20:26,525 --> 00:20:27,754
(SCOFFS)

418
00:20:28,461 --> 00:20:29,826
What?

419
00:20:30,763 --> 00:20:32,925
In the cookie jar, sir.

420
00:20:32,998 --> 00:20:34,488
(LAUGHS)

421
00:20:34,567 --> 00:20:37,537
We got motive.
We got opportunity.

422
00:20:37,603 --> 00:20:41,198
And once we pick up the murder weapon,
we got you.

423
00:20:52,685 --> 00:20:54,449
Right to the wall
with me, huh, Dennis?

424
00:20:54,520 --> 00:20:56,614
Don't start. Beth's
waiting in the squad room.

425
00:20:56,689 --> 00:20:59,681
Thanks. No, thanks a lot,
since my right to consult with an attorney

426
00:20:59,759 --> 00:21:01,921
is recognized under
the law, but thanks.

427
00:21:01,994 --> 00:21:04,361
Knock it off, okay? There's
nothing for me to feel guilty about,

428
00:21:04,430 --> 00:21:05,420
so don't even try.

429
00:21:05,498 --> 00:21:07,330
You told them
I carry a .38.

430
00:21:07,399 --> 00:21:09,060
Like that information's
not in the computer?

431
00:21:09,135 --> 00:21:10,933
My cookie jar
isn't in the computer.

432
00:21:11,003 --> 00:21:12,903
At least, it wasn't.

433
00:21:12,972 --> 00:21:14,269
(INDISTINCT CHATTERING)

434
00:21:14,373 --> 00:21:15,807
(PHONE RINGING)

435
00:21:16,442 --> 00:21:18,171
Hi.
We can go to my office,

436
00:21:18,244 --> 00:21:19,939
but I thought you could
use some coffee first.

437
00:21:20,012 --> 00:21:21,844
Thanks, Dennis. Do you believe that moron,
Chapman's

438
00:21:21,914 --> 00:21:24,042
trying to hang
a murder rap on me?

439
00:21:24,116 --> 00:21:25,982
Punching people out all the
time? What the hell you expect?

440
00:21:26,051 --> 00:21:28,042
Oh, when did I become
the town bully?

441
00:21:28,120 --> 00:21:31,488
Monckton's the guy that has
a problem in that area, not me.

442
00:21:31,557 --> 00:21:33,047
Had a problem.

443
00:21:33,125 --> 00:21:34,593
What'd you do to your hair?

444
00:21:35,427 --> 00:21:38,021
Nothing. I just
let it go natural.

445
00:21:38,130 --> 00:21:39,928
Well, you don't have curly hair,
you have straight hair.

446
00:21:39,999 --> 00:21:41,797
You've always
had straight hair.

447
00:21:41,867 --> 00:21:44,802
I used to have it straightened,
Jim. I don't any more.

448
00:21:45,771 --> 00:21:47,261
I liked it straight.

449
00:21:47,339 --> 00:21:48,966
I didn't.

450
00:21:49,041 --> 00:21:51,032
You used to wear suits.

451
00:21:51,110 --> 00:21:52,703
Oh, you don't like
what I have on?

452
00:21:52,778 --> 00:21:55,679
I didn't say that. No, no,
what you have on is fine.

453
00:21:55,748 --> 00:21:57,443
(CHUCKLING) Well,
it's a little casual,

454
00:21:57,516 --> 00:21:59,484
considering the
circumstances, but...

455
00:21:59,552 --> 00:22:01,452
You wake me up in
the middle of the night...

456
00:22:01,520 --> 00:22:04,148
ROCKFORD: Oh, come on,
it's hardly the middle of the night, Beth.

457
00:22:04,223 --> 00:22:06,817
It is for those of us who
didn't get to bed until 2:30.

458
00:22:06,892 --> 00:22:08,656
We ought to take this
into the office.

459
00:22:08,727 --> 00:22:10,695
After four years of not
hearing one word from you,

460
00:22:10,763 --> 00:22:14,028
I get a call from Dennis saying
big surprise, you're in trouble.

461
00:22:14,099 --> 00:22:15,225
For privacy.

462
00:22:15,301 --> 00:22:16,791
I drag myself down here,

463
00:22:16,869 --> 00:22:19,463
don't ask me why,
old habits die hard, I guess.

464
00:22:19,538 --> 00:22:21,404
And what do I get?
"Thanks? Nice to see you?"

465
00:22:21,473 --> 00:22:25,000
No, I get a critique on my hair
style and a dress code alert.

466
00:22:25,077 --> 00:22:27,102
Guys, we're starting
to draw a crowd.

467
00:22:27,179 --> 00:22:28,476
CHAPMAN: Becker...

468
00:22:28,781 --> 00:22:31,341
Beth... No, wait, wait,
wait, wait, wait, wait, wait.

469
00:22:31,417 --> 00:22:34,876
Now, I know it's been a while,
but it hasn't been any four years.

470
00:22:34,954 --> 00:22:36,945
Four years,
practically to the day.

471
00:22:37,022 --> 00:22:39,252
How do I know that?
Because I took you out to lunch.

472
00:22:39,325 --> 00:22:42,420
A very nice lunch to celebrate
the publication of my first book.

473
00:22:42,494 --> 00:22:44,622
We had champagne,
which neither of us like, particularly,

474
00:22:44,697 --> 00:22:47,428
but it seemed appropriate. I gave
you an autographed copy of the book,

475
00:22:47,499 --> 00:22:49,524
and that, as they say,
was that.

476
00:22:49,602 --> 00:22:51,570
(SIGHS) That was
four years ago?

477
00:22:51,637 --> 00:22:53,833
When it actually made the
New York Times Best-Seller List,

478
00:22:53,906 --> 00:22:56,204
I thought,
"Oh, he's gotta call now."

479
00:22:56,275 --> 00:22:58,004
It was on the list
for over a year.

480
00:22:58,077 --> 00:22:59,670
Nineteen months,
for the sake of accuracy.

481
00:22:59,745 --> 00:23:01,611
My second book
did even better.

482
00:23:02,781 --> 00:23:05,045
(STUTTERING) I don't...
I don't know what to say.

483
00:23:05,117 --> 00:23:07,108
You've got a right
to be sore.

484
00:23:07,186 --> 00:23:08,654
Hey, it's history.

485
00:23:08,721 --> 00:23:09,813
Well, Beth,
where are you going?

486
00:23:09,889 --> 00:23:12,859
Home. I don't practice law any
more. I haven't practiced it in years.

487
00:23:12,925 --> 00:23:15,690
Well, isn't it kind of
like riding a bicycle?

488
00:23:15,761 --> 00:23:17,160
You can't leave me now.
You're good.

489
00:23:17,229 --> 00:23:19,527
I need good. I need your knowledge,
your expertise.

490
00:23:19,598 --> 00:23:20,622
And?

491
00:23:20,699 --> 00:23:22,326
Your ability to carry me
for a couple of months.

492
00:23:22,401 --> 00:23:25,496
Four, tops. You know,
I gotta put my trailer back together.

493
00:23:25,571 --> 00:23:27,403
That's gonna take
what little I have.

494
00:23:27,473 --> 00:23:29,965
I want you to file a separate
suit against this department

495
00:23:30,042 --> 00:23:33,910
for malicious destruction
of property. Major damages.

496
00:23:33,979 --> 00:23:38,007
Flattered as I am, let me put
this so you'll understand it, Jim.

497
00:23:38,083 --> 00:23:40,347
If I were practicing law,
which I am not,

498
00:23:40,419 --> 00:23:42,353
it would be
a polar day in hell

499
00:23:42,421 --> 00:23:44,719
before I'd ever
represent you again.

500
00:23:44,790 --> 00:23:46,724
And I don't like
your hair either.

501
00:23:49,695 --> 00:23:51,254
Where's she going?
Well, it doesn't matter.

502
00:23:51,330 --> 00:23:52,764
We don't need her anyway,
right now.

503
00:23:52,831 --> 00:23:54,822
Why don't we need her?
Not that we have her.

504
00:23:54,900 --> 00:23:58,029
Your .38 wasn't there,
so they decided not to charge you.

505
00:23:58,103 --> 00:24:00,731
At least, not yet. Too
circumstantial without the weapon.

506
00:24:00,806 --> 00:24:02,365
What do you mean
it wasn't there?

507
00:24:02,441 --> 00:24:04,808
They looked in the cookie
jar. They found Oreos.

508
00:24:04,877 --> 00:24:06,572
Did they look
under the Oreos?

509
00:24:06,645 --> 00:24:09,740
These are trained police officers. Of
course, they looked under the Oreos.

510
00:24:09,815 --> 00:24:11,783
It wasn't there. Go home.

511
00:24:19,458 --> 00:24:23,452
You know, this would go a lot
faster if you'd stop trying to help me.

512
00:24:23,529 --> 00:24:25,554
Well, tell me what to do.

513
00:24:25,631 --> 00:24:30,091
The temptation is strong.
Look, I do this all the time.

514
00:24:30,169 --> 00:24:32,263
You leave me alone for a
few minutes and I'll have it up.

515
00:24:32,338 --> 00:24:34,136
Look good as new.
It is new.

516
00:24:34,206 --> 00:24:35,970
(GRUNTS) Well,
the cops busted it.

517
00:24:36,041 --> 00:24:37,907
If you ask me,
they ought to pay for it.

518
00:24:37,977 --> 00:24:39,206
These things are expensive.

519
00:24:39,278 --> 00:24:40,439
I noticed.

520
00:24:41,113 --> 00:24:42,581
What makes them special?

521
00:24:42,648 --> 00:24:45,276
Anybody ever tell 'em,
"You bust it, you buy it?"

522
00:24:45,351 --> 00:24:48,377
Probably not.
Want some coffee, George?

523
00:24:48,454 --> 00:24:49,819
Nah.

524
00:24:49,888 --> 00:24:51,515
JESS: May I have a cup?

525
00:24:55,294 --> 00:24:58,594
Jess Wilding. I don't know
if you remember me or not.

526
00:25:00,332 --> 00:25:03,734
Nobody forgets
the IRS, Miss Wilding.

527
00:25:03,802 --> 00:25:08,035
Come on in. Take inventory.
Slap a lien on something.

528
00:25:21,053 --> 00:25:22,418
You've made a few changes.

529
00:25:22,488 --> 00:25:24,547
Not all of them
were my idea.

530
00:25:37,870 --> 00:25:39,429
(SIGHS)

531
00:25:40,372 --> 00:25:42,602
Is that going to be it
for the small talk?

532
00:25:46,478 --> 00:25:48,105
I'm not here on business.

533
00:25:49,748 --> 00:25:51,113
What else is there?

534
00:25:51,183 --> 00:25:52,810
There's personal.

535
00:25:59,892 --> 00:26:02,122
It's so amazing.

536
00:26:02,194 --> 00:26:03,958
You could charge
for this view.

537
00:26:05,431 --> 00:26:06,921
I don't.

538
00:26:12,504 --> 00:26:14,336
Why are you so hostile?

539
00:26:14,406 --> 00:26:15,464
(LAUGHS)

540
00:26:15,541 --> 00:26:17,134
You're the IRS,
you tell me.

541
00:26:17,209 --> 00:26:19,303
It can't be the first time
you've had this reaction.

542
00:26:19,378 --> 00:26:22,075
Oh, you still can't be sore
about that audit I gave you.

543
00:26:22,147 --> 00:26:23,876
I was more than fair with you.

544
00:26:23,949 --> 00:26:27,783
Fair? You disallowed deductions that
are key to the operation of my business.

545
00:26:27,853 --> 00:26:30,948
What? Dinner and the Lakers
with Dennis Becker?

546
00:26:31,023 --> 00:26:33,321
Lieutenant Becker.
He's a cop.

547
00:26:33,392 --> 00:26:34,655
He's a friend.

548
00:26:35,694 --> 00:26:39,562
Can't wait to tell him that's now
common knowledge on a federal level.

549
00:26:39,631 --> 00:26:41,861
You're not at all like
your father, you know.

550
00:26:42,835 --> 00:26:44,360
After I did your audit,
he took me to dinner.

551
00:26:44,436 --> 00:26:47,667
He said that I'd worked hard
and I earned a good supper.

552
00:26:47,739 --> 00:26:49,400
Yeah, sounds like Rocky.

553
00:26:50,843 --> 00:26:52,777
I was in Switzerland
when he...

554
00:26:54,313 --> 00:26:55,542
I---

555
00:26:55,614 --> 00:26:58,845
I didn't hear about his
death until I came back home.

556
00:27:01,120 --> 00:27:03,817
I bought him a cuckoo clock.
You know, a little one.

557
00:27:04,890 --> 00:27:07,416
I really think he would've
gotten a kick out of that.

558
00:27:08,894 --> 00:27:11,090
You two stayed in touch?

559
00:27:11,163 --> 00:27:13,894
I didn't know that.
Rocky never mentioned it.

560
00:27:17,035 --> 00:27:19,402
I'd like to visit his grave,
if you don't mind.

561
00:27:20,506 --> 00:27:21,905
Oh, yeah, sure.
Of course.

562
00:27:23,108 --> 00:27:24,542
I'll write the directions
out for you.

563
00:27:24,610 --> 00:27:26,044
No, I don't mean that.

564
00:27:27,179 --> 00:27:29,147
I'd like you to
go there with me.

565
00:27:30,315 --> 00:27:32,215
I think Rocky would want that.

566
00:27:46,565 --> 00:27:48,294
God, I'm going to miss him.

567
00:27:58,577 --> 00:27:59,874
Are you all right?

568
00:27:59,945 --> 00:28:03,108
(SNIFFS) Yeah. Sorry.
I swore I wouldn't do this.

569
00:28:13,625 --> 00:28:16,617
Well, you and Rocky must've
spent quite a lot of time together.

570
00:28:16,695 --> 00:28:19,426
I'm surprised I never
ran into you at the ranch.

571
00:28:19,498 --> 00:28:22,058
Well,
you always used to call before you came up,

572
00:28:22,134 --> 00:28:25,798
so when I'd get a call from Rocky saying,
"Can we make it next weekend?"

573
00:28:25,904 --> 00:28:28,066
I knew it was because
you were there.

574
00:28:28,140 --> 00:28:30,438
I don't think he wanted
to share you.

575
00:28:30,509 --> 00:28:31,977
Or you.

576
00:28:32,044 --> 00:28:34,604
I got a few of those
phone calls, too.

577
00:28:34,680 --> 00:28:36,512
You're having trouble
with that, aren't you?

578
00:28:36,582 --> 00:28:38,209
You're having trouble
with the idea that Rocky

579
00:28:38,283 --> 00:28:39,580
could have a relationship
with somebody,

580
00:28:39,651 --> 00:28:40,914
and you wouldn't know
anything about it.

581
00:28:40,986 --> 00:28:42,681
Hey, it's none
of my business.

582
00:28:42,754 --> 00:28:45,883
You know, Rocky didn't
just exist in a vacuum.

583
00:28:45,958 --> 00:28:48,723
You know, he was more
than just your father.

584
00:28:48,794 --> 00:28:51,195
Isn't it great you turned
up to point that out?

585
00:28:51,263 --> 00:28:53,755
I might never have figured
that out on my own.

586
00:28:55,834 --> 00:28:57,359
Rocky was not
a secretive man.

587
00:28:57,436 --> 00:28:58,767
He was an open book.

588
00:28:58,837 --> 00:29:00,999
Well,
looks like you missed a couple of chapters.

589
00:29:01,073 --> 00:29:03,440
Yeah, well keeping me out of the
loop wouldn't have been his idea.

590
00:29:03,508 --> 00:29:05,203
"Keeping you
out of the loop"?

591
00:29:05,277 --> 00:29:07,507
Oh, forget it. I don't even know
why I'm trying to talk to you.

592
00:29:07,579 --> 00:29:09,445
You're certainly not
anything like your father.

593
00:29:09,514 --> 00:29:11,312
Yeah. Well, neither are you.

594
00:29:14,086 --> 00:29:17,488
(BOTH LAUGHING)

595
00:29:23,295 --> 00:29:24,490
(SIGHS)

596
00:29:25,397 --> 00:29:26,558
Fresh start?

597
00:29:26,632 --> 00:29:28,191
I'd like that.

598
00:30:03,235 --> 00:30:05,101
There's a car following us.

599
00:30:05,170 --> 00:30:07,002
Been with us since
the top of the hill.

600
00:30:07,072 --> 00:30:09,370
Well, he doesn't have much
choice. There's only one road out.

601
00:30:09,441 --> 00:30:13,036
That's what I thought. But when I stopped,
he stopped, too.

602
00:30:13,111 --> 00:30:14,237
So what are you going to do?

603
00:30:14,313 --> 00:30:15,405
Lose him.

604
00:30:15,480 --> 00:30:16,845
(CAR ENGINE STARTING)

605
00:30:17,983 --> 00:30:19,883
(TIRES SQUEALING)

606
00:30:41,373 --> 00:30:44,809
He's driving like a crazy person!
He came that close to hitting me!

607
00:30:44,876 --> 00:30:46,708
He's going south
on Sepulveda.

608
00:30:46,778 --> 00:30:50,373
You better get the cops out
here before he kills somebody!

609
00:30:50,449 --> 00:30:52,042
(TIRES SQUEALING)

610
00:31:01,727 --> 00:31:03,422
(CARS HONKING)

611
00:31:06,164 --> 00:31:07,461
(SCREAMS)

612
00:31:28,387 --> 00:31:29,684
Hang on.

613
00:31:30,889 --> 00:31:32,789
(CAR BRAKES SQUEALING)

614
00:31:43,802 --> 00:31:45,395
(LAUGHING)

615
00:31:46,405 --> 00:31:47,600
You're good.

616
00:31:54,913 --> 00:31:56,210
MAN: Hey, watch it!

617
00:32:14,766 --> 00:32:16,234
Damn!

618
00:32:19,137 --> 00:32:21,538
What the hell do you think you're
doing? You trying to kill somebody?

619
00:32:21,606 --> 00:32:22,971
What, you think I don't
know what you've been doing?

620
00:32:23,041 --> 00:32:24,304
You think I wasn't
gonna find out?

621
00:32:24,376 --> 00:32:26,003
Don't do that.
Mr. Gustavo, if you'll just...

622
00:32:26,077 --> 00:32:27,943
Who put you up to this?
Get back in the car, Jess.

623
00:32:28,013 --> 00:32:29,742
What should I do? What should
I do? I said don't shove me.

624
00:32:29,815 --> 00:32:30,805
Now, I want names, damn it!

625
00:32:30,882 --> 00:32:32,077
Don't shove me, damn it!

626
00:32:32,150 --> 00:32:33,345
(BOTH GRUNTING)

627
00:32:33,418 --> 00:32:34,647
(SIREN WAILING)

628
00:32:34,719 --> 00:32:36,084
Hit him, Jim!
Just hit him!

629
00:32:36,154 --> 00:32:37,588
Get back in the car, Jess.

630
00:32:37,656 --> 00:32:39,249
Hit him!
Get back in the car!

631
00:32:41,927 --> 00:32:44,521
LEWIS ON PA: You two,
break it up. Step away from the vehicle.

632
00:32:46,465 --> 00:32:49,924
Okay, everybody settle down.
You all right, sir?

633
00:32:50,001 --> 00:32:51,628
Why don't you ask me
if I'm all right?

634
00:32:51,703 --> 00:32:53,398
You all right?
Yeah.

635
00:32:53,472 --> 00:32:55,736
I'm gonna file assault
charges against this man.

636
00:32:55,807 --> 00:32:58,504
You want to file charges? You're
the reason for this whole mess.

637
00:32:58,577 --> 00:33:00,875
Officer, he was following us.

638
00:33:01,680 --> 00:33:02,977
His car's in front of yours.

639
00:33:03,048 --> 00:33:05,540
He's been following me
for over a week.

640
00:33:05,617 --> 00:33:07,642
You ask him
if that's not true.

641
00:33:07,719 --> 00:33:11,656
You ask him if he hasn't been questioned
in the death of one of my employees,

642
00:33:11,723 --> 00:33:13,851
if he isn't the
number one suspect.

643
00:33:14,693 --> 00:33:16,684
It's a long story.

644
00:33:16,761 --> 00:33:18,126
Maybe I struck first.

645
00:33:18,196 --> 00:33:20,927
You bet you struck first.
I'm a witness, Officer.

646
00:33:20,999 --> 00:33:23,468
Well, if I did,
it was in self-defense.

647
00:33:23,535 --> 00:33:25,663
I was afraid
he was carrying a gun.

648
00:33:25,737 --> 00:33:26,966
Check the car.

649
00:33:27,038 --> 00:33:28,267
Allow me.

650
00:33:28,340 --> 00:33:31,503
I mean, for all I know,
I may be next on his list.

651
00:33:31,576 --> 00:33:33,510
The police officer
I spoke with,

652
00:33:33,578 --> 00:33:34,943
a Captain Chapman,

653
00:33:35,013 --> 00:33:38,074
he said they've been trying
to put him away for years.

654
00:33:38,149 --> 00:33:39,639
Look what I found.

655
00:33:42,387 --> 00:33:43,912
(SIGHS)

656
00:33:43,989 --> 00:33:45,548
MARTINEZ: You have the
right to remain silent.

657
00:33:45,624 --> 00:33:48,753
Anything you say, can and will be
used against you in a court of law.

658
00:33:48,827 --> 00:33:50,022
You have the right
to an attorney.

659
00:33:50,095 --> 00:33:51,654
If you cannot afford one,
one will be provided for you...

660
00:34:12,984 --> 00:34:14,645
(INDISTINCT CHATTERING)

661
00:34:22,294 --> 00:34:23,853
Excuse me, I wonder
if you could help me.

662
00:34:23,929 --> 00:34:25,055
I'm looking for
Lieutenant Becker.

663
00:34:25,130 --> 00:34:26,256
He's not in his office.

664
00:34:26,331 --> 00:34:28,959
Becker? No,
ma'am. He's in Commander Diehl's office.

665
00:34:29,034 --> 00:34:32,368
(CHUCKLES) Been there a
lot lately. I think he's in trouble.

666
00:34:33,505 --> 00:34:35,098
(LAUGHING)

667
00:34:42,080 --> 00:34:43,878
They seem quite busy today.

668
00:34:43,949 --> 00:34:44,973
Mmm.

669
00:34:45,050 --> 00:34:46,484
Are you here to confess?

670
00:34:48,119 --> 00:34:49,211
Excuse me?

671
00:34:49,287 --> 00:34:50,755
Well, I don't
mean to pry, but,

672
00:34:50,822 --> 00:34:54,383
I have been here for 45 minutes,
and you just came in.

673
00:34:56,094 --> 00:34:57,584
I'm an attorney.

674
00:34:57,662 --> 00:34:59,892
Oh, I don't need one.
I did it.

675
00:35:00,665 --> 00:35:01,723
Oh.

676
00:35:02,300 --> 00:35:03,597
(CHUCKLES)

677
00:35:04,269 --> 00:35:05,293
(SNICKERS)

678
00:35:05,370 --> 00:35:07,737
(STAMMERING) I'm just...
I'm just going...

679
00:35:07,806 --> 00:35:09,467
(MAN SHOUTING)

680
00:35:09,541 --> 00:35:10,667
Bye.

681
00:35:11,343 --> 00:35:14,074
Hi, Sally. SALLY: Good morning,
Commander.

682
00:35:22,053 --> 00:35:25,079
I may have to get myself
a larger office.

683
00:35:25,156 --> 00:35:26,555
Did you get
everybody's statement?

684
00:35:26,625 --> 00:35:28,286
No, sir, I was
waiting for you.

685
00:35:29,427 --> 00:35:31,020
Thank you.

686
00:35:31,096 --> 00:35:35,465
Oh, you've been spending so much time here,
you're practically family.

687
00:35:35,533 --> 00:35:37,558
So, where do we start?

688
00:35:37,636 --> 00:35:40,264
Well, could we start with a
couple of industrial strength aspirin?

689
00:35:40,338 --> 00:35:41,703
I have the worst headache.

690
00:35:41,773 --> 00:35:44,674
You're a real chronic complainer,
aren't you, Rockford?

691
00:35:44,743 --> 00:35:46,734
You always gotta find
something to bellyache about.

692
00:35:46,811 --> 00:35:48,336
Do you have an aspirin?

693
00:35:48,413 --> 00:35:49,812
I don't get headaches.

694
00:35:49,881 --> 00:35:52,407
Yeah? Well, you give 'em.

695
00:35:52,484 --> 00:35:54,077
Jess?
Sorry.

696
00:35:54,152 --> 00:35:55,210
Dennis?

697
00:35:55,286 --> 00:35:59,120
Becker doesn't have any aspirin,
Rockford. Nobody here has any aspirin.

698
00:35:59,190 --> 00:36:01,056
Could we please
just get on with this?

699
00:36:01,126 --> 00:36:03,686
I can lay it out for you in very
simple terms, Commander.

700
00:36:03,762 --> 00:36:04,752
He was following me.

701
00:36:04,829 --> 00:36:06,160
Right away, that's a lie!

702
00:36:06,231 --> 00:36:07,426
He followed us.

703
00:36:07,499 --> 00:36:09,797
I was following them
because he was following me.

704
00:36:09,868 --> 00:36:12,530
You know, believe it or not,
that actually makes sense.

705
00:36:12,604 --> 00:36:14,299
HECTOR: After what happened
to Bud Monckton

706
00:36:14,372 --> 00:36:15,840
and Mr. Rockford's
involvement in that...

707
00:36:15,907 --> 00:36:17,204
I had no involvement in that.

708
00:36:17,275 --> 00:36:19,972
I wanted to know why
I was being followed.

709
00:36:20,045 --> 00:36:22,013
I demanded to know
who hired him.

710
00:36:22,080 --> 00:36:23,172
Your wife hired him.

711
00:36:23,248 --> 00:36:24,272
What?

712
00:36:24,349 --> 00:36:25,783
Damn it, Chapman,
that's inexcusable.

713
00:36:25,850 --> 00:36:28,114
But... That's
privileged information.

714
00:36:28,186 --> 00:36:31,087
You can't just blat out something
that was told to you in confidence.

715
00:36:31,156 --> 00:36:32,248
My wife?

716
00:36:33,024 --> 00:36:34,287
Yeah. Yeah, Linda.

717
00:36:34,359 --> 00:36:37,522
Uh, 52", 5'3",
exotic looking.

718
00:36:37,595 --> 00:36:40,530
I'm not married.
I've never been married.

719
00:36:41,399 --> 00:36:44,391
Your friend, Randy Silvero,
recommended me.

720
00:36:45,737 --> 00:36:48,035
